Reviewed outside colonoscopy and pathology and radiology reports.  His CT is on QREADS.
IMPRESSION
#1 Colorectal cancer in the setting of FAP
Discussed cancer staging treatment and surveillance with the patient and his wife as well as the disease entity of FAP.  We discussed the various surgical options including IPAA and Brooke ileostomy.  The patient will undergo further staging with repeat colonoscopy and EUS for a rectal cancer as well as an extended EGD with side-viewing scope to assess for upper GI neoplasms.  CT enterography will also be requested to rule-out small-bowel polyps and desmoid.  His outside CT will be sent to Radiology for interpretation.  The patient will be asked to meet with stoma therapy for ileostomy education and will meet with Colorectal Surgery for surgical recommendations.  The patient understands that if indeed this is rectal cancer and is T3 or N1, neoadjuvant chemoradiation will be advised prior to surgical resection.
Discussed with Dr. Lindsay Johnson, note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

